 gas depletion time varies with\nsSFR, it is mostly independent of mass, indicating that the low L$_{CO}$/SFR\nratios long observed in low mass galaxies are entirely due to photodissociation\nof CO, and not to an enhanced star formation efficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Feb 2017 02:32:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-02"}
